1
00:00:07,132 --> 00:00:08,133
Hiroshi here.

2
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:10,636
I am dancing more
than usual these days.

3
00:00:10,636 --> 00:00:12,638
But that's because
it feels like some sort

4
00:00:12,638 --> 00:00:14,556
of overwhelmingly
incredible power

5
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:17,059
is coming closer and
closer all the time!

6
00:00:17,059 --> 00:00:21,104
Expel evil spirits
and promote our welfare!

7
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:23,065
(screams)

8
00:00:23,065 --> 00:00:24,650
♪

9
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:26,568
I told them not
to make it painful.

10
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:28,278
‐(doorbell chimes)
‐It's me, Noi!

11
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:30,322
I brought some cake!

12
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,825
Let's all fight over it
together, okay, you guys?

13
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,494
(engine revving)

14
00:00:35,494 --> 00:00:37,079
(scream)

15
00:00:37,079 --> 00:00:42,501
♪

16
00:00:42,501 --> 00:00:44,711
(gasps)

17
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:47,422
It's...Auntie!

18
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,508
‐What's goin'‐‐
‐(scream)

19
00:00:49,508 --> 00:00:51,677
(thuds)

20
00:00:51,677 --> 00:00:53,553
Uh...hi, Auntie.

21
00:00:55,222 --> 00:00:57,766
Emergency!

22
00:00:57,766 --> 00:01:00,352
(sirens wailing)

23
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:04,815
‐What's going on?
‐I'm sleepy!

24
00:01:04,815 --> 00:01:07,818
(screaming)

25
00:01:07,818 --> 00:01:09,403
Are you in there, Sunako?

26
00:01:09,403 --> 00:01:10,487
(screaming)

27
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:11,863
Open this door!

28
00:01:11,863 --> 00:01:14,241
I'm not going to, I can't,
there's no friggin' way,

29
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:15,534
I can't do this...

30
00:01:15,534 --> 00:01:17,244
♪

31
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:19,246
Make it extra‐large,
s'il vous plaît.

32
00:01:19,246 --> 00:01:20,706
Roger.

33
00:01:20,706 --> 00:01:24,960
‐(slamming thud)
‐(scream)

34
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:26,712
What...is this?

35
00:01:26,712 --> 00:01:28,755
No, don't look!

36
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:35,929
Uh, um...this is...

37
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:38,932
(indistinct crosstalk)

38
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:41,310
Just...

39
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:44,646
Just look at that!

40
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:49,818
♪

41
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:57,743
(wailing)

42
00:01:57,743 --> 00:02:00,245
What for?

43
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:02,497
Um...uh...

44
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:05,083
Have some cake
if you like, it's salty.

45
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:07,002
Sunako!

46
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:08,670
Why don't we go to a spa?

47
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:09,671
Huh?

48
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:11,673
I've arranged to
unveil you at a party

49
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:14,384
the day after tomorrow.

50
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:16,845
Is that okay?

51
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,138
Why so suddenly?

52
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,931
Being self‐centered, as always.

53
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:22,434
‐Do you want me to whip you?
‐No, ma'am!

54
00:02:22,434 --> 00:02:25,937
Let's begin by getting
rid of stuff like this!

55
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:27,773
(screech)

56
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:32,027
♪

57
00:02:32,027 --> 00:02:33,570
Su‐‐Suna‐‐

58
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,530
(screams)

59
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:39,618
♪

60
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:44,289
Why...why is Sunako so...

61
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:46,041
Please have some
tea if you like,

62
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,459
but it's not hot anymore.

63
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:48,502
Like it or not,

64
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:50,420
Sunako's much better
than she was before.

65
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:53,215
Right, now she's becoming‐‐
or getting settled closer to‐‐

66
00:02:53,215 --> 00:02:54,466
becoming a lady!

67
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:56,802
Yeah, we're working two percent
faster than the leading brands.

68
00:02:56,802 --> 00:02:58,595
She cleans and does
laundry better than anyone,

69
00:02:58,595 --> 00:02:59,805
and she cooks like a pro!

70
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:02,516
It's funny, but I don't
recall ever having asked you

71
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:05,644
to turn my beloved niece
Sunako into a housewife.

72
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,104
No, ma'am, you didn't.

73
00:03:07,104 --> 00:03:09,690
I had no idea!

74
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:13,276
But I must get Sunako to that
party the day after tomorrow

75
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:14,444
no matter what!

76
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:16,905
Heh, don't gimme that crap
after you suddenly show up

77
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:17,906
out of the blue.

78
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:19,700
You need to give her
a little more time.

79
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,076
Would she be ready in two days

80
00:03:21,076 --> 00:03:23,495
if I gave her
a little more time?

81
00:03:23,495 --> 00:03:25,664
Auntie, do you remember
when we first moved in here,

82
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:26,998
you told us all kinds of things,

83
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:28,500
but you were still
watching over us.

84
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,419
As you did with us,
you should treat Sunako

85
00:03:30,419 --> 00:03:32,587
‐with patience and dignity.
‐No way.

86
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:33,672
First of all,

87
00:03:33,672 --> 00:03:35,549
when I foolishly let you
degenerates move in here,

88
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:36,925
I was totally
out of my mind,

89
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:38,051
I mean, what was I...

90
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:40,303
(voice speeds up to gibberish)

91
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:41,638
No way.

92
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:44,266
No lecture for me, thank you.

93
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:50,063
♪

94
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,189
(whimpers)

95
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:52,190
Auntie.

96
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:54,109
If you've got
something to say to her‐‐

97
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:55,193
(screams)

98
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:57,529
‐‐then you need to say
whatever it is to her face.

99
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,281
(angry gibberish)

100
00:03:59,281 --> 00:04:01,074
I can't stand this, I can't.

101
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:02,492
Please try to hang on, Noi.

102
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,244
Why am I still here?

103
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,580
There ya go.

104
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:07,539
(gasps)

105
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:09,124
Sunako!

106
00:04:09,124 --> 00:04:10,375
Are you excited?

107
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:13,462
It'll be a beautiful
and fabulous party!

108
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:16,798
Geez, why didn't you say no
right away like you always do?

109
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:18,717
♪

110
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:21,761
Say no?

111
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:25,182
Would you say no even
if I begged you this way?

112
00:04:25,182 --> 00:04:28,226
She's ultra radiant!

113
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:30,562
Another nosebleed!

114
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:32,022
It's getting worse!

115
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:33,732
Break, you have to break now!

116
00:04:33,732 --> 00:04:34,941
Listen.

117
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,027
Don't you remember you managed
to tolerate looking pretty

118
00:04:37,027 --> 00:04:38,445
a couple times before?

119
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:41,531
Maybe you can put up
with it just one more time?

120
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:42,449
Uh‐uh!

121
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:43,492
I know.

122
00:04:43,492 --> 00:04:44,868
What if I could
offer you a reward

123
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:46,369
if you can do it again?

124
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:47,829
Re‐ward?

125
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:48,747
What do you want?

126
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:50,123
Some banned video?

127
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,417
Or perhaps some internal
organs for Hiroshi?

128
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:54,795
Uh‐uh!

129
00:04:54,795 --> 00:04:55,879
No thanks.

130
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:59,257
What I want is to do
something fun with Auntie.

131
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:00,300
Huh?

132
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:03,428
Will you become a normal...

133
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:04,429
Mm‐hm!

134
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:06,932
‐Will you become a normal‐‐
‐Normal housewife?

135
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:10,769
Yes, Auntie will become
a normal house‐‐what?

136
00:05:10,769 --> 00:05:13,271
Mm‐hm!

137
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:15,607
(unhinged laughter)

138
00:05:15,607 --> 00:05:19,820
She was so shocked that
she completely lost it.

139
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,738
What, do you mean that's
really all you want?

140
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:22,948
Yes!

141
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:24,074
All right, then.

142
00:05:24,074 --> 00:05:25,784
If doing that's going to
help make you into a lady,

143
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:28,161
‐then it'll be an easy task.
‐Oh, really?

144
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:31,248
‐Costume, s'il vous plaît.
‐Roger.

145
00:05:31,248 --> 00:05:38,171
♪

146
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,464
What do you think?

147
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:40,882
Maid service!

148
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:43,093
‐(exclaims)
‐I don't get it.

149
00:05:43,093 --> 00:05:44,553
I don't get it at all!

150
00:05:44,553 --> 00:05:46,930
What is supposed to be
housewifey about that?

151
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:48,348
I don't look like a housewife?

152
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,016
Putting your
appearance aside for now,

153
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:51,977
can you actually
behave like a housewife?

154
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:53,728
Well, my maids took care
of all the housework

155
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:54,980
when I first got married.

156
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,565
Then I traveled the
world with my business,

157
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:59,109
so I've never done a single
chore around the house.

158
00:05:59,109 --> 00:06:00,735
Jealous!

159
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,487
Auntie, I'll show you how.

160
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:05,031
So why don't we try doing
the housework together?

161
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:06,700
‐Together?
‐When it's nice outside,

162
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,994
you enjoy the sunlight
and air out the futons.

163
00:06:08,994 --> 00:06:10,078
On rainy days,

164
00:06:10,078 --> 00:06:12,038
you sit quietly in front
of the fireplace and knit.

165
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,498
You enjoy your
day‐to‐day life

166
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:15,083
and cook delicious meals.

167
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,376
And now we're going to indulge

168
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,378
in that placid
lifestyle together.

169
00:06:18,378 --> 00:06:21,172
Lovely, such a lovely lifestyle!

170
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:23,133
‐Auntie!
‐Sunako!

171
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:24,634
Does this mean
they made a deal?

172
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:25,886
Now our rent's gonna be free.

173
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:27,220
I can't believe
the day's coming

174
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,764
when I get to clean
and do laundry with Auntie.

175
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:32,183
I mean, I just...can't wait!

176
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:35,353
I'll start down the road
to housewifeliness tomorrow.

177
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:37,814
Housewife, housewife, woo‐hoo!

178
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:39,900
Um, I know I shouldn't
say it, but...

179
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,484
I'm just not sure about this.

180
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:43,028
It's just that I‐‐

181
00:06:43,028 --> 00:06:45,322
‐I agree.
‐Ditto.

182
00:06:45,322 --> 00:06:47,782
(gong ringing)

183
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,870
♪

184
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,246
Morning comes for two women

185
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:56,041
with drastically different
images of a housewife.

186
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,460
You pour the detergent
here and press the switch.

187
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,587
The machine will do
everything else automatically.

188
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:02,631
Okay!

189
00:07:02,631 --> 00:07:05,050
(applause)

190
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:08,261
‐Boys, I'm exhausted.
‐Already?

191
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:10,597
‐So next is‐‐
‐Why don't we have some tea?

192
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:11,723
Seriously?

193
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:14,059
But there're so many
things we need to do.

194
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:14,934
Huh?

195
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,102
I'm gonna go vacuum now,

196
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:18,396
and I want you to hang these
clothes on the line to dry.

197
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:19,648
Then when you're done with that,

198
00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:21,566
I want you to do
another load of laundry.

199
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:22,484
Sure.

200
00:07:22,484 --> 00:07:24,778
Well, I have
a bad feeling about‐‐

201
00:07:24,778 --> 00:07:26,029
Stop right there.

202
00:07:26,029 --> 00:07:27,322
Sunako's having fun.

203
00:07:27,322 --> 00:07:28,573
You were right, Noi.

204
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:29,491
You know what?

205
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:33,036
Sunako must really
like Auntie a lot.

206
00:07:33,036 --> 00:07:35,497
(giggling)

207
00:07:35,497 --> 00:07:37,082
(humming over vacuum's roar)

208
00:07:37,082 --> 00:07:38,958
Oh, we're going digital now‐‐

209
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:41,378
Sunako, do you need any help?

210
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:44,005
No, but you might
want to help Auntie.

211
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:45,090
Oh, speaking of Auntie,

212
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:47,467
I saw her put the dirty laundry
in the limousine earlier

213
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:49,177
‐and then drive off.
‐What?

214
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:50,845
‐Drive where?
‐To the shopping arcade,

215
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,889
‐she said.
‐You coulda told us sooner.

216
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,432
My bad.

217
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:57,060
Auntie!

218
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:59,270
Time it took for Auntie
to abandon housework:

219
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:01,022
Two minutes and
seventeen seconds.

220
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,441
I knew something like
this would happen.

221
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:04,818
My bad!

222
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:06,361
♪

223
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:08,571
Where are you, Auntie?

224
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,281
Ah, hello!

225
00:08:10,281 --> 00:08:11,783
(scream)

226
00:08:11,783 --> 00:08:14,577
‐I knew you'd slack off.
‐I'm not slacking.

227
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:16,579
I was doing laundry.

228
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,708
I've taken everything
to the cleaners.

229
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,626
Since they said it was
going to take a few days,

230
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:25,463
I bought replacement clothes,
just look at all the goodies.

231
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:27,298
Hello, madam, see our meat?

232
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,591
‐What's that?
‐The highest quality

233
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:29,634
domestic beef.

234
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:31,511
100 grams for 10,000 yen.

235
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:33,805
This tuna costs 500,000 yen.

236
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:35,849
Half a dozen matsutake
mushrooms, 20,000 yen each.

237
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:37,475
I'll take them all,
s'il vous plaît.

238
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:38,560
Auntie!

239
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:39,728
Today you're only
supposed to buy

240
00:08:39,728 --> 00:08:40,854
some squid at the fish market

241
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:42,981
and some daikon radish
at the grocer.

242
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,190
That's boring.

243
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:45,942
That's entirely
beside the point.

244
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:47,485
Fine, I'll just have one daikon.

245
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:48,653
Here.

246
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:49,696
That's 180 yen.

247
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:50,822
Use this.

248
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:53,992
But, miss, we only take
cash, not phone cards.

249
00:08:53,992 --> 00:08:56,119
Never mind, just forget it!

250
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:59,748
You know I haven't ever
shopped on foot before.

251
00:08:59,748 --> 00:09:01,541
My goodness, Sunako.

252
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:04,002
Why, young man, you over there!

253
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:06,755
‐Yes?
‐Will you carry these groceries?

254
00:09:06,755 --> 00:09:08,423
Huh?

255
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:10,633
‐With pleasure.
‐What?!

256
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,802
Never mind us, please don't
pay any attention to her,

257
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,054
have a nice day.

258
00:09:14,054 --> 00:09:18,266
Housewives are not supposed
to enslave passersby, okay?

259
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:20,477
Hm...hm...hm?

260
00:09:20,477 --> 00:09:21,811
Oh, never mind!

261
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:25,857
♪

262
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:36,242
♪

263
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:37,243
(marveling)

264
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:39,079
Wow, it looks like a movie set.

265
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,539
Since Sunako told me we were
going to have oden today,

266
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:42,999
we set it up like this.

267
